                       "message":  "AUDIT-CLEANUP-PIEGATE-LINTDOC: Save-As PIE-gate test + ARCHITECTURE_LINTS 9-\u003e10 lint-count fix\n\nTwo independent post-audit cleanups (tests + docs only; 0 production logic,\n0 Cargo.toml), drained as one tightly bounded dispatch before the menu-wiring\nfrontier.\n\n1. crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/tests.rs - add\n   save_as_new_project_outside_editing_is_noop, mirroring\n   save_outside_editing_is_noop. Locks the Ctrl+Shift+S Save-As PIE gate\n   (save_request.rs:357): during Play the handler returns BEFORE the dialog /\n   new-project hook, so a mid-Play Save-As can never persist the transient\n   play-state world to a brand-new on-disk .rge-project. Asserts the hook\n   call-count is 0, save_source stays None, and play_state is unchanged.\n\n2. docs/§18/ARCHITECTURE_LINTS.md - correct the lint-count / enumeration drift\n   throughout. The doc presented the suite as \"9 lints\" / \"Cmd::All runs all 9\"\n   / \"adding the 10th lint\" (as if the 10th were unbuilt); ground truth is 10 =\n   9 enforcement lints + the supplementary warning-level snapshot-participate\n   (main.rs:59-67,97-111; 10 src/*.rs lint modules; 10 tests/*_test.rs). README\n   and main.rs\u0027s own doc already use the \"9+1\" framing - this doc was the lone\n   outlier giving a wrong count in isolation (the lone Layer-1 audit finding).\n   Fixed: the status/count claims, §2 table (+snapshot-participate row), §3\n   (+a snapshot-participate block), §5 test enumeration + verified sub-totals\n   (33-\u003e38 inline, 64-\u003e69 integration, 107 total; snapshot_participate.rs 378L /\n   5 inline + snapshot_participate_test.rs 5 integration), §10 guidance, §12\n   References, and stale main.rs line-refs (88-99-\u003e97-111, 38-60-\u003e38-67). §11\u0027s\n   authoring-time reconciliation is preserved with a note pointing to the\n   corrected current figures.\n\nProvenance: 2026-06-01 read-only 5-axis deep audit - test-coverage TOP PICK\n(P2 data-integrity) + the lone Layer-1 doc-drift finding (P2).\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
