                       "message":  "AUDIT-CLEANUP-PIEGATE-LINTDOC: correction — fix 2 missed current-state test counts (#286)\n\nCodex NEEDS_CORRECTION (docs-only). The lint-count fix updated §5\u0027s test totals\nto 107 / 38 inline + 69 integration but missed the SAME counts restated as\ncurrent-state prose on two lines:\n- docs/§18/ARCHITECTURE_LINTS.md:5 (Status row): \"97+ ... (33 inline + 64\n  fixture-based integration)\" -\u003e \"107 ... (38 inline + 69 fixture-based\n  integration)\".\n- docs/§18/ARCHITECTURE_LINTS.md:20 (§1, third load-bearing property):\n  \"Test count today: 97+ across all lints.\" -\u003e \"107 across all lints.\"\n\nRoot cause: the post-edit stale-prose sweep grepped for the \"9-lint\" framing,\nnot the old numeric values (97 / 33 / 64). A whole-file re-grep for the old\ntokens now leaves only the §11 authoring-time bullet (intentionally kept, with\nits framing note) + a main.rs line-ref (97-111).\n\nDocs-only; the new test and the rest of the doc fix are unchanged.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
